{
  "stem": "13623.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They would call names to make sure that everybody is there, and there was some people that would skip and not show up certain times.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There were days that they would come to the house and just arrest a 12-year-old or older.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he was put into the local jail for a couple of days, and he was let out.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And slowly things were happening where a man in the village-- mostly it would be a Hasidic man-- when they were going on the street, walking on the street, or going into another town just for fun they would shave a half a beard off him-- leave a half off just, just for fun.",
      "word_count": 54
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And there was no recourse.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Nobody can go to report anything.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Nobody would-- there was not even any thought about going to the police because even though the-- our local population's there, not the police themselves, the, the people just took it and they said, thank God that's all that happened to me.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They always-- people always thought worse things than this can happen.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We don't know what can happen, but if they just cut half a beard off, we'll have to learn with it.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It happened to my uncle.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It didn't happen to anybody closer than that in my family that I can remember.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My father, being that he was a cattlemen, he knew a lot of people, a lot of Gentiles that he did a lot of business with them.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He was one of the most well-known people in the town, and there were many things that he was not picked on as much as some other people were picked on during that period.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Another, another law came out that Jewish merchants cannot be-- cannot do business anymore.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
